Abuja – Marvin records First Lady, Tiwa Savage has been confirmed as Pepsi Ambassador, following speculations of her being dropped. The confirmation was necessary following issues in her marriage which trended on social media over the weekend. The Managing Director of Seven Up Bottling Company, Mr Sunil Sawhney took to his twitter account to deny reports that the singer had been dropped as Pepsi Ambassador. “I will like to clarify that our relationship with Tiwa Savage is as strong as ever.’’ he wrote. “Following this clarification by Mr Suni Sawhney, the contract with Tiwa Savage is not due to end anytime soon as the singer still remains the brand ambassador. (NAN)